			<h1>Stiefel History</h1>
			<h2>Imbibe the Intoxicating History of the Stiefel</h2>
			<h4>To delve into the history of the Stiefel, one must accept that genius is highly coveted and prone to imitation. In this case, the birthplace of the legendary Stiefel is claimed by more than one culture. Research has uncovered similar historical accounts in the Austrian and German annals of Stiefel lore. Although this site is based on the German Stiefel tradition, it is not overly important with whom the credit of conceiving the Stiefel is placed. Honestly!</h4>
			<h4>The central lesson of the dual claims to the Stiefel is that the Stiefel is not only accepted by different cultures, it is held in high-enough esteem to be native to two different cultures. The Stiefel, in theory and definitely in practice, transcends cultural and ethnic boundaries, which often are seen as barriers to social interaction. At any party/event, the Stiefel can literally be passed to every person, dismissive of all stereotypes or prejudices, willing to give completely of itself for the enjoyment of all, leaving behind a wake of positive social interactions born from the shared experience of Passing the Stiefel.</h4>
			<h4>Now, the True ‘Stiefel’ original stories …</h4>
			<h2>The German Legend</h2>
			<h4>The catalyst for the Stiefel, grounded in the German tradition, was of all things, war. Quite the polar opposite of what the Stiefel stands for … or is passed around for, but in a sense it could be what we all strive for. </h4>
			<h4>During an intense battle in Europe, the exact battle and war has been lost to time, a German military commander sought to inspire, galvanize his struggling troops. With a keen mind, he understood the core motivation behind his soldier’s morale and made them a solemn promise midway through battle. “Men, as we stand upon the verge of victory or defeat, you all must believe in my commitment to you my brave countrymen. Take up your arms, and fight till victory is ours before the sun sets on our chance for glory, and you shall witness your humble commander, in your honor, savor the beer of our country in the very boots I stand in right here, right now.” Well, the very thought of this tremendous feat their commanding officer, the soldiers returned to battle with courage and grit and rallied to overcome their adversaries.</h4>
			<h4>As the sun set on the battlefield, victory was placed at the feet of the German commander and his soldiers, who now stood in anticipation of the fulfillment of their commander’s vow. That very night, as the full moon dressed the commander in an auspicious glow, he raised in salute to his troop’s gallant fight in combat, the very boot he wore during the battle, filled to the brim with beer and drank with his men cheering on. At that very instance the boot was born … and the rest is history. The next time it came for the commander to drink from the boot, he had glassmaker fashion a glass boot — The Stiefel — which would be henceforth passed to all the men who were strong enough to fight, and strong enough to Pass the Stiefel</h4>
			<h2>The Austrian Legend</h2>
			<h4>In the Austrian tradition the Stiefel represents the fulfilling and replenishing elements found in the rarest of places. </h4>
			<h4>In mid-April, a group of men and women set out on an arduous trek through the Austrian Alps to bring supplies to a mining outpost in the mountain range that suffered from the year’s extreme winter which stranded the post for months.</h4>
			<h4>Midway into the trek’s first day, they were overcome with the insatiable desire to quench their thirst. Although, they had started with the sun well below the peaks and the dew upon the mountain grass, the day had grown hot and they began to tire as the sun grew toward its zenith in the sky. They had not anticipated such a strong sun, as the spring months offered softer highnoons and more tolerable sun. Left on the path without any beverage, even water, the possibility of satisfying the growing longing for any liquid faded away along with the town they had left that morning. Call it blind luck, or a serendipitous discovery, but as they rounded the very next pass, they happened upon a solitary hut, nestled very comfortably in a shady nook of the mountain.</h4>
			<h4>At once their hope fluttered, but slowly waned as successive knocks on the door yielded only silence. However, just as they were turning away, an old man whipped open the door and appeared to their amazement. “Don’t go running away just yet. I was just rearranging my pantry and didn’t hear you till just now.” Well the group of weary trekkers wasted no time explaining to the old man their dilemma and pleaded for any act of kindness. The old man was more than generous, when he offered the last of his cherished ale to them all. “I can’t drink it all” he surmised “And what better than with new friends to share a beer and the beauty of the Alps.” “One small problem, I don’t have any glasses.” Well, only a brief second passed, and without pausing one of the women sat with a grace that had drained out of the rest of the group and pulled out a pair of boots from her knapsack. It has a pair that had not been worn, for she was bringing them as a gift to her sister at the outpost. “This boot will do” she said and passed it to old man, who grinned with a twinkle in his eye. “Ah, I see, let me get the ale.” So the group settled in, and enjoyed the company of the old man and each other, slowly passing the boot among each other and washing away all remnant of thirst.</h4>
			<h4>The Stiefel was born to bring reprieve to harsh day and to bring strangers together only to part as friends. In the grand scheme of the Stiefel, it doesn’t matter with which historical account one identifies more strongly. Anyone can make their history with the Stiefel, simply by passing it to the person on their right and allowing the fun to begin. Whether one needs to celebrate a hard fought victory; relax from a hard week of school or work, or both; and whether sharing a Stiefel with old friends or new friends, the Stiefel stands to bring people together and to celebrate any and all reasons that can transpire as one holds and Passes the Stiefel.</h4>
			<h4>Cheers!! Next, the Stiefel Game.</h4>
